reviewText:
Alright this is my second reveiw on this game. I love transformers, love it..........and this game ruined it. In terms of the actual game it's fine, graphics are fine. Cybertron segments are ok, Earth segments are awful (the lighting, reflections and shadows were exceptional). Ok now, from what the game description says, the Earth side of the game is the sequel to age of extinction, i went and watched the movie. This is no were near sequel, absolute rubbish. I'm thinkin that the developers were out of ideas, this 'Dark Spark' is entirely new. Was not part of the original transformers franchise. Also, u don't get to use prime's new sword, dissapointing. Now as for the cybertron side, prequel of fall of cybertron. Not really, the missions were really random. The only thing that related to FOC was the mentioning of the ark and trypticon. On the plus side, escalation is a big improvement as i mentioned in my previous review. But anyway, Highmoon Studios must be laughing like crazy.

COME BACK HIGHMOON AND SHOW EM WHAT A TRANSFORMERS GAME SHOULD LOOK LIKE.

/// Buy this game at your own risk \\ Do not buy if your interested in storyline, maybe buy it if your interest lies in gameplay.
